The inter-relationship of herpes virus, papilloma 16/18 virus infection and Pap smear pathology in Israeli women. A previous survey of the seroprevalence of the herpes virus type 2 (HSV-2) infection in Israel provided us with an opportunity to study a) the prevalence of human papillomavirus (HPV) 16/18 in selected groups of women b) the correlation between the infection with HSV-2, HPV-16/18 and Papanicolaou (PAP) pathology